{
  "stem": "21349.3",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Till finally, I found a place not far from the [INAUDIBLE], Bremen [NON-ENGLISH] it's called.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And not far from the hotel where Hitler had killed [NON-ENGLISH] in 1934, also in Bremen.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And [CLEARS THROAT] I said, can we have this?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He said, yes, you can have it, but only two or three times a week and in the afternoon.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But I had a problem then, because we had to have teachers-- no teachers.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So I just told a few merchants and people who were just coming back from concentration camps how to teach them.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So we taught them little things.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We taught them a little bit about Jewish things, about history, about having gymnastics, a little bit of English, a little bit of geography-- where they would be going to.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we had 42 children, 42 children from all parts around Bremen, the surroundings, boys and girls between 6 and 12 years old, I think.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Some of them, I still met-- I met later on in New York.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Two of them I met in New York, and I'm still in contact with them.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, I was asked by the community in [NON-ENGLISH] [NON-ENGLISH] means where the raise-- or the river front flows into the North Sea.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It's not far from Bremerhaven.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And also Bremerhaven, to come there and to talk to them about immigration.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So when I did this-- because I did a few translations for the Hebrew Immigrant Aid Society-- Yeah, I went there.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I instituted some causes.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Not too often, because I spent only two or three months there.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, he knew.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Parchman, Parchman knew.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[LAUGHS]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Once, once, that was the only time I ever went to Berlin.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was on January 18th, 1939.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
